l DVD; they allow you to get exactly what you want out of your conversion.","There are some major downsides to this otherwise excellent program. Chief among them is that it creates bloated video files. When we converted a feature-length Hollywood movie, the resulting file was a whopping 8.1GB. By comparison the rest of the products we reviewed generally yielded a video file between 2-3.5GBs. This bloat means that you’ll be able to fit less movies on your iPad.","A larger file may be acceptable if it produced a higher-quality conversion. Unfortunately, this is not the case. When compared to a digital download of the same movie, the quality of the converted DVD didn’t justify the large file size. When we inspected the converted video, we noticed slight pixilation and some scaling blur.","The audio portion of the conversion was similarly average. The details are not as rich as the original, and some of the finer details are degraded. Neither of these flaws are a deal breakers. But given the massive file size, it is surprising that the quality of converted file is anything less than perfect."]},"id":"61a037f6-5234-47f9-b508-880604e68baa","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Summary"},"id":"b5a85715-91b8-4d6e-a3eb-9df4ed343ca3","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["Tipard DVD Ripper does a lot of things right: It’s easy to use, offers conversion profiles for every single iPad, and it offers basic video editing tools that allow you to customize your conversion to fit your exacting needs. But it has some major flaws: It produces bloated files that you don’t correlate with higher quality as well as compromised sound quality."]},"id":"54723c38-c057-43b0-9756-5431001459b9","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"product_review_page_52408","url":"/tipard-review","authors":[{"email":"","slug":"danny-chadwick","url":"/author/danny-chadwick","dateCreated":"2019-04-05T10:05:21Z","name":"Danny Chadwick","dateModified":"2019-04-05T10:05:21Z","id":"DhF8Hg8QQde8MtLyq8X8JN","dateImport